<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key D (2 sharps: F#, C#). "33" root triads dominate; "333" for D7 cadences.
- Non-diatonic: Bb+ → D (①), C#°7 → G (④), G#° → G (④). All substituted diatonic.
- Bm7 = ③m, Em7 = ②m. A7/A = ⑤7/⑤.
- LH always 4 notes in open voicing. RH 2 notes, third/sixth pairs.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH F#2 appears consistently in D-chord measures as leading tone pedal.
- RH descends bar 5-6 (C6→B5→A5) as melody climbs, providing contrary motion.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opens gently (bar 1), builds through the rising melody bars 5-6, climaxes bar 10-11.
- Two-phrase form (bars 1-8, 9-16). Final D cadence straightforward root position.
-->
